      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WHERE'S THE LUCK (8) won again in another strong performance to make it two on the bounce, scoring by one length (17.51) at this track over 300m. Well placed and will be tough to beat. TANGLES TIPPETT (4) finished third (17.67) two back at this track but out of the placings last time when 6th there. Form here at the trip sound including five wins. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Should be about the mark. NITRO FREDDIE (2) boxed on well to finish third last time, beaten 0.8 lengths (17.57) behind Just A Joy at this track. Solid formlines coming through his last run. Expected to be in the finish again. AL CAN DO (7) is another with top-three prospects.",
